 <h3 class=3D"secondary-headline"></h3>
 <div class=3D"full-width-callout">
  <p><b>Other factors to bear in mind</b></p>
  <p>While the IRS currently does not issue digital asset-specific penaltie=
s, the agency is indeed increasing its scrutiny around these assets, which =
in turn raises users=E2=80=99 risk of examination and existing penalties. A=
 few things to bear in mind:</p>
  <ul>
   <li>The default limitation on assessments is three years under IRC 6501(=
a).<sup>viii</sup></li>
   <li>If a taxpayer under-reports gross income by more than 25%, the limit=
ation on assessment is six years under IRC 6501(e).<sup>ix</sup></li>
   <li>In the case of fraud=E2=80=94when a user purposefully files a return=
 with incorrect information to attempt to evade taxes=E2=80=94the IRS has u=
nlimited time to assess.=20
    <ul>
     <li>It=E2=80=99s possible that failure to report ownership of digital =
assets by acknowledging them on your Form 1040 could subject you to this ex=
tended statute.</li>
    </ul></li>
   <li>The IRS is increasingly using John Doe summonses to find account hol=
ders.</li>
  </ul>
 </div><!--language div end-->
</div></div></div>
